{"lemma":"عَرَفات","slug":"عَرَفات","root":"ع.ر.ف","root_slug":"ع-ر-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ر-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَرَفات","root":"عرف","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28741"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AA"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28741","headword_ar":"عَرَفَاتٌ","root":"Erf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mountain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where the pilgrims halt"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, O, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the day of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earafap","text_ar":"عَرَفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[above mentioned], (O, K,) [described by Burckhardt as a granite hill, about a mile, or a mile and a half, in circuit, with sloping sides, rising nearly two hundred feet above the level of the adjacent plain,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"said to be nine miles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twelve miles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from Mekkeh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K;) said by J to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at, Minè,"},{"kind":"text","text":"but incorrectly, (K, TA,) unless thereby be meant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near Minè;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) also called by some ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earafapu","text_ar":"عَرَفَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, Msb;) but the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazalonaA Earafapa","text_ar":"نَزَلْنَا عَرَفَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nazalotu biEarafapa","text_ar":"نَزَلْتُ بِعَرَفَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I, alighted at"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earafap","text_ar":"عَرَفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",] is like a post-classical phrase, (S, O, K,) and (S, O) it is said to be (Msb) not genuine Arabic: (S, O, Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarafaAtN","text_ar":"عَرَفَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a [proper] name in the pl. form, and therefore is not itself pluralized: (S, O, K:) it is as though the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarafapN","text_ar":"عَرَفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to every distinct portion thereof: (TA:) as Fr says, it has, correctly, no sing.; (S, O;) and it is determinate as denoting a particular place; (Sb, S, O, K, TA;) and therefore not admitting the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Sb, TA;) differing from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~ayoduwna","text_ar":"الزَّيْدُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[because this is a proper name common to a number of persons]: you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`w^ulaA='i EarafaAtN","text_ar":"هٰوُلَا=ءِ عَرَفَاتٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HasanapF","text_ar":"حَسَنَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"These are 'Arafát, in a good state"},{"kind":"text","text":"], putting the epithet in the accus. case because it is indeterminate [as a denotative of state, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSad~iqFA","text_ar":"مُصَدِّقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wahuwa AlHaq~u muSad~iqFA limaA maEahumo","text_ar":"وَهُوَ الحَقُّ مُصَدِّقًا لِمَا مَعَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur ii. 85]: (S, O:) it is decl. ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSoruwfapN","text_ar":"مَصْرُوفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[more properly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEorabapN","text_ar":"مُعْرَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t","text_ar":"ت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is equivalent to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musolimiyna","text_ar":"مُسْلِمِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musolimuwna","text_ar":"مُسْلِمُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) the tenween becoming equivalent to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":", therefore, being used as a proper name, it is left in its original state, like as is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musolimuwna","text_ar":"مُسْلِمُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"when used as a proper name: (Akh, S, O, K:) [i. e.,] it is decl. in the manner of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musolimaAtN","text_ar":"مُسْلِمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^ominaAtN","text_ar":"مُوْمِنَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the tenween being like that which corresponds to the masc. pl. termination"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":", not the tenween of perfect declinability, because it is a proper name and of the fem. gender, wherefore it does not admit the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarafaAtN","text_ar":"عَرَفَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"was thus named because Adam and Eve knew each other ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEaArafaA","text_ar":"تَعَارَفَا"},{"kind":"text","text":") there (IF, O, K, TA) after their descent from Paradise: (TA:) or because Gabriel, when he taught Abraham the rites and ceremonies of the pilgrimage, said to him “ Hast thou known? ” ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEarafota","text_ar":"اَعَرَفْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (O, K,) and he replied “ I have known ” ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earafotu","text_ar":"عَرَفْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (K:) or because it is a place sanctified and magnified, as though it were rendered fragrant ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eur~ifa","text_ar":"عُرِّفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuy~iba","text_ar":"طُيِّبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (O, K:) or because the people know one another ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yataEaArafuwna","text_ar":"يَتَعَارَفُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":") there: or, accord. to Er-Rághib, because of men's making themselves known ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nitaEar~ufi AlEibaAdi","text_ar":"نِتَعَرُّفِ العِبَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":") there by religious services and prayers. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","O","Msb","K","TA","S","Akh","IF"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}